      "message": "Yes, it goes through the regular function-call path for intrinsics that don\u0027t have a case in this switch.\n\nThe workarounds in writeFunctionCall are meaningful/valid for intrinsics too. They allow swizzled out-params to work (and are otherwise harmless). In practice this is meaningful for `modf` and `frexp`; without the workaround code, passing a swizzle to modf would generate invalid Metal.\n\nWe do have a test for this: http://osscs/skia/skia/+/main:tests/sksl/intrinsics/Modf.metal?q\u003dModf.metal",
